
### man_1_simple_shell

```markdown
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2024" "Simple Shell Manual" "Version 1.0"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple command-line interpreter that reads user commands and executes them.

.SH OPTIONS
This shell does not support any command-line options.

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit [STATUS]
Exits the shell. If a numeric status is provided, the shell exits with that status.

.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment.

.SH EXAMPLES
To run the shell:
.PP
$ ./hsh
.PP
To list files in the current directory:
.PP
$ ls -l
.PP
To exit the shell:
.PP
$ exit

.SH AUTHORS
See the AUTHORS file for the list of contributors.

.SH SEE ALSO
.B bash (1)